26:08.000 --> 26:20.000
Yes, we use guerrilla marketing. On the one hand, we try to analyze which territory we are operating on, and then we try to analyze which territory our competitor is operating on.

26:20.000 --> 26:36.000
We identify the territory, just as the guerrillas did during the Second World War or during the Napoleonic Wars. The task is the same. We identify a weak point and strike there, and as inconspicuous as possible.

26:37.000 --> 26:58.000
The task of guerrilla marketing is the same. There is a concept of camouflage. Indeed, the best option is to save money and nerves, and you will get the best result.

26:58.000 --> 27:17.000
