01:05:28.000 --> 01:05:42.000
There are events, one after another. There are annual events, there are events aimed at the future. Strategic marketing tries to put all this together.

01:05:58.000 --> 01:06:25.000
All these things, in the end, were built into a marketing plan. There is a product, it is oriented to certain needs. There is a market, there is a market dynamics.

01:06:25.000 --> 01:06:41.000
We try to segment this market, to identify priority segments, plan our events, and in the end we should get what? We should get a sales forecast, and this should be planned in the long term.

01:06:41.000 --> 01:07:00.000
At the moment, most companies, including yours, are not ready to answer the question of what sales we will have. We assume that, based on the analysis of previous periods, we will sell for 2 million last summer.

01:07:00.000 --> 01:07:19.000
This month we will probably sell for 2 million, or we will, or we won't. We don't know this. We just assume. Why? We don't know the factors that shape the market, and we can't say, next year I will earn 2 million, and if I do this, I will earn 3 million.

01:07:19.000 --> 01:07:37.000
Therefore, it makes sense to invest money in these events. By the way, if we take marketing events, again, the same as one of the examples, pay attention, both in the world and in Russia, the BTL sector is increasing. What is this connected with?

01:07:37.000 --> 01:07:58.000
What attracts advertisers to BTL? Theoretically, it gives instant results. The company is trying to leave the strategy and tactics sectors. BTL events were held, and it was either effective or ineffective. The question is solved.

01:07:59.000 --> 01:08:23.000
We planned a long-term program, a media plan for a year or two, for example, God forbid, for 15 years. How to evaluate it? Are you ready to sign a deal that will have such a volume of sales, and, based on this, we can allocate such a volume of money for advertising events, promotion events, or something else?

01:08:23.000 --> 01:08:39.000
Are we ready to invest in industrial development or something else? It is clear that no. Russia is a very indicative country in this regard. Why? Pay attention.

01:08:39.000 --> 01:08:59.000
Russia is the only country where there are experimental companies that feed on the new scientific and technical developments. Almost all customers are Western companies, and they work for the order. Russian companies do not risk working with this.

01:08:59.000 --> 01:09:23.000
We all know that the source of super-profit in any market is innovation. What is innovative in Russia? Nothing special. We all know where the money is coming from. Thank God, we have a lot of oil, and the oil prices are rising.

01:09:23.000 --> 01:09:34.000
The same strategic marketing planning can be presented in three elements. We cannot make a plan right away.

01:09:54.000 --> 01:10:12.000
We have to make a plan based on the situation in the country, on the price of education, on the change of the assortment policy, on the promotion policy, and so on.

01:10:12.000 --> 01:10:26.000
We have to implement this plan. We have to put it on paper, build a system of key parameters, and only then can we implement it. We cannot build a plan and implement it right away.

01:10:27.000 --> 01:10:45.000
The question whether we are ready to name the key parameters based on which we will manage marketing is one of the key questions. If you are not ready, you will not be able to implement the business process.

01:10:45.000 --> 01:11:14.000
We all know the Pareto rule, 20 to 80, 9 to 90, it does not matter. The main idea of the Pareto rule, the ABC system, and all the other things that are the basis of management, we all know what is the key in our activities, and what is less important.

01:11:15.000 --> 01:11:29.000
